New York City Rental Affordability Analysis

This R Notebook analyzes NYC sales data and integrates it with spatial data for commercial boundaries and mandatory inclusionary housing (MIH). The project includes data cleaning, merging, regression analysis, and data visualization using scatterplots and spatial maps to study affordability and property characteristics.

Note: Unfortunately, the mapview visualizations cannot be rendered here. For a detailed view and better understanding of the project, please visit: https://kikossik.github.io/portfolio/p1-ny-mih/.

Note2: Comments inside cells are very useful for those who want to dig deeper inside the code.

Visualizing Data on a Map


library(leaflet)
library(leaflet.extras)
library(sf)

# Reproject all datasets to WGS84
Sales_draw <- st_transform(Sales, crs = 4326)  # Transform to WGS84
MIHSF_draw <- st_transform(MIHSF, crs = 4326)
Commercial_bounds_draw <- st_transform(Commercial_bounds, crs = 4326)

# Extract coordinates from the reprojected Sales_sample
Sales_coords <- st_coordinates(Sales_draw)

# Create a data frame with longitude and latitude
Sales_coords <- data.frame(
  lon = Sales_coords[, 1], 
  lat = Sales_coords[, 2] 
)

# Create the leaflet map with a reddish/pink gradient
heatmap <- leaflet() %>%
  addProviderTiles("CartoDB.DarkMatter") %>%
  # Add the heatmap layer with a custom reddish gradient
  addHeatmap(
    lng = ~lon,
    lat = ~lat,
    data = Sales_coords,
    blur = 5,
    max = 1,
    radius = 10,
    gradient = c(
      "0" = "#ffe6e6",  # Very light red
      "1" = "#ff0000"
    )
  ) %>%
  # Add MIHSF polygons
  addPolygons(
    data = MIHSF_draw,
    color = "mediumturquoise",
    weight = 4,
    fillOpacity = 0.9,
    group = "MIHSF"
  ) %>%
  # Add Commercial_bounds polygons
  addPolygons(
    data = Commercial_bounds_draw,
    color = "yellow",
    weight = 2,
    fillOpacity = 0.9,
    group = "Commercial Bounds"
  ) %>%
  # Add layers control
  addLayersControl(
    overlayGroups = c("Sales Heatmap", "MIHSF", "Commercial Bounds"),
    options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = FALSE)
  )
